{
  "text": "The naked mole rat is an exceptionally long-lived species, with a lifespan four times longer than similarly sized rodents, thus making the naked mole rat an important model for longevity studies [CITATION_1] . Naked mole rats do not have typical lifespan curves in which mortality rates increase with age, but rather they experience few of the biological changes typically associated with aging such as decreased metabolic rate, body composition changes, and declines in genomic and proteomic integrity [CITATION_2] . Naked mole rats are resistant to age-associated diseases such as cancer [CITATION_3] , cardiac diastolic dysfunction [CITATION_4] , and neurodegenerative diseases [CITATION_5] . Thus, the naked mole rat represents a naturally occurring, unique model of healthy aging.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "13598294",
    "[CITATION_2]": "5265074",
